-- 
Thousands Protest Hungary Constitution, Austerity, Index Reports

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-04-18T06:08:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/thousands-protest-hungary-constitution-austerity-index-reports.html
Thousands of Hungarians protested
in Budapest against the country’s new constitution and planned
austerity measures,  Index n ews website reported.  Former Prime Minister  Ferenc Gyurcsany , of the opposition
Socialist Party, as well as Lehet Mas a Politika, another
opposition group, participated in separate demonstrations
against the constitution, which Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s
coalition plans to approve today over an opposition boycott,
Index reported.  Some 15,000 law enforcement workers, including police and
firefighters, held other demonstrations to protest the scrapping
of early retirement entitlements, Index said.  To contact the reporters on this story: Zoltan Simon in Budapest
at   zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  